    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spheres-rods system composed of 3 spheres placed side-by-side and connected by two horizontal rods. The two outer spheres each have a mass of m, and the center sphere has a mass of 2 m. A vertical axis is drawn through the center of each sphere. The axes are labeled, from left to right, axis 1, axis 2, and axis 3. The outer axes are each separated by a distance d from the center axis.\" src=\"/images/f22047e0a07af3b0f58b94a7a56ae7ee.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three spheres, with masses indicated in the figure, are connected by rods of negligible mass. The spheres-rods system makes a rigid body. Axes <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> are also indicated in the figure. The rotational inertia of the spheres-rod system about Axis <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, Axis <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and Axis <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l sub 1\"><math alttext=\"l sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, <span class